    "en": {
      "title": "A new train from Kankasanthure to Murukkandi",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Focusing on the demand for trains, a new train from Kankasanthure to Kilinochchi Murukkandi started running yesterday (11).",
        "This slow train will start its journey from Kankasanthure station at 6.00 am and reach Kilinochchiya station at 7.50 am and Murukkandi station at 8.11 am.",
        "The train departs from Murukkandi railway station at 8.30 am and reaches Kankasanthure station at 10.41 am.",
        "The train departs from Kankasanthure station at 2.00 pm and reaches Murukkandi station at 4.10 pm and departs from Murukkandi station at 4.40 pm to reach Kankasanthure station by 7.00 pm.",
        "According to the request of Fisheries Minister Douglas Devananda, the Railway Department deployed this train on the instructions of Transport and Highways Minister Dr. Bandula Gunawardena.",
        "Dr. Bandula Gunawardena, Minister of Transport and Highways, said that the new train was added for the convenience of the passengers in the Northern Province in order to maintain their daily activities without interruption due to the fuel crisis that people are currently facing and due to the fact that bus fares are very high."
      ],
